{
  "text": "To date, various methods have been developed and introduced to extract features from ECG signals. One commonly used method is the heart rate variability analysis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . HRV analysis is a broadly used method in biomedical engineering applications [CITATION_4] . The method developed by Ferdinando et al. [CITATION_5] using HRV analysis had an accuracy of around 59% for identifying arousal and valence state of a person. Similarly, another study that developed an emotion recognition model incorporating ECG signals and skin resistance had 80% accuracy for recognizing the four quadrants of the discrete emotional model [CITATION_6] .",
  "correct_citation": {
